1
00:00:01,324 --> 00:00:04,895
It is said that life's
encounters are governed by fate.

2
00:00:04,895 --> 00:00:07,030
Tangled up in the threads of fate...

3
00:00:07,030 --> 00:00:09,633
...are the ill-fated blossoms,
pitiful and frail.

4
00:00:09,633 --> 00:00:14,171
Lost in anger, sorrow, and tears...

5
00:00:14,171 --> 00:00:16,907
Beyond the veil of midnight,

6
00:00:16,907 --> 00:00:20,243
the retribution that you are
helpless to reap shall be yours.

7
00:00:23,613 --> 00:00:29,085
A butterfly, hanging upside down,
that will head towards the light sometime

8
00:00:29,085 --> 00:00:34,257
The reflection in the mirror
as we cut our hair

9
00:00:34,257 --> 00:00:39,629
Footsteps echoing
in the hallway during class

10
00:00:39,629 --> 00:00:44,901
The sound of rain follows us ceaselessly

11
00:00:44,901 --> 00:00:52,676
Purely what we feel is blinding
and can take the shape of a sweet flower

12
00:00:52,676 --> 00:00:55,378
Or the shape of a poisonous fruit

13
00:00:55,378 --> 00:00:58,114
Rain again today

14
00:00:58,114 --> 00:01:05,355
I want to link that day to now, sky-to-sky

15
00:01:05,355 --> 00:01:07,991
In this craziness, uncertainty

16
00:01:07,991 --> 00:01:15,966
Will we be able to leave a trace
of each of our emotions somewhere?

17
00:01:15,966 --> 00:01:18,768
In this craziness, you gave me life

18
00:01:18,768 --> 00:01:26,610
To what bounds can we
safeguard one emotion?

19
00:01:26,610 --> 00:01:29,279
In this craziness, uncertainty

20
00:01:29,279 --> 00:01:37,387
Will we be able to leave a
trace of each of our selves somewhere?

21
00:01:37,387 --> 00:01:40,056
In this craziness, you gave me life

22
00:01:40,056 --> 00:01:48,293
To what bounds can we
safeguard each of our selves?

23
00:02:12,088 --> 00:02:14,648
"Please, help me."

24
00:02:15,058 --> 00:02:16,826
That one again, eh?

25
00:02:16,826 --> 00:02:19,596
Day in and day out. Talk about persistent.

26
00:02:19,596 --> 00:02:22,827
But you decided not to
take that request, right?

27
00:02:35,078 --> 00:02:37,247
Are we being ignored again today?

28
00:02:37,247 --> 00:02:39,482
I swear...

29
00:02:39,482 --> 00:02:41,416
J-Just a little longer...

30
00:02:43,386 --> 00:02:44,788
That's enough for today.

31
00:02:44,788 --> 00:02:45,588
What?

32
00:02:45,588 --> 00:02:48,091
Oh, hello? It's me!

33
00:02:48,091 --> 00:02:52,084
I'm starving! How about
we go grab a bite to eat?

34
00:02:53,363 --> 00:02:57,834
Yeah, I'm at the office right now. See you!

35
00:02:57,834 --> 00:03:01,604
Man, if only I could make
the acquaintance of Hell Girl,

36
00:03:01,604 --> 00:03:05,375
this company could easily double in size.

37
00:03:05,375 --> 00:03:09,004
Oh, but if that happened,
I guess you'd be out of a job.

38
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:11,915
I'll see you bright and early tomorrow.

39
00:03:11,915 --> 00:03:15,485
What? I have final exams tomorrow.

40
00:03:15,485 --> 00:03:17,287
There's a board meeting.

41
00:03:17,287 --> 00:03:21,849
Misato, who do you think you even
owe the fact that you're in school?

42
00:03:42,912 --> 00:03:46,404
"Dead Line Incorporated
Dead Line Incorporated Reception
Dead Line Incorporated
Asano Planning, Inc."

43
00:03:49,219 --> 00:03:50,587
Good night.

44
00:03:50,587 --> 00:03:52,521
Good night, I'll be going now.

45
00:03:58,261 --> 00:04:00,729
"Fujimi Housing"

46
00:04:14,577 --> 00:04:20,116
"The Woman in the Tall Tower"

47
00:04:20,116 --> 00:04:21,150
"Dead Line Incorporated"

48
00:04:21,150 --> 00:04:23,820
"Dead Line Incorporated"
Yes, the online shop Dead Line

49
00:04:23,820 --> 00:04:24,353
Yes, the online shop Dead Line

50
00:04:24,353 --> 00:04:27,123
is a company our president,
Riho Kaifu, started

51
00:04:27,123 --> 00:04:29,751
with a couple friends
when she was a student.

52
00:04:30,726 --> 00:04:35,198
Ms. Riho is the only one
left of the original founders,

53
00:04:35,198 --> 00:04:39,802
but with her rich knowledge of
computers and business acumen,

54
00:04:39,802 --> 00:04:44,073
she's grown the company
to this size in just 4 years!

55
00:04:44,073 --> 00:04:46,409
She must be an incredible woman.

56
00:04:46,409 --> 00:04:49,512
All the employees look up to her.

57
00:04:49,512 --> 00:04:52,982
Can you believe it?! In just 4 years!

58
00:04:52,982 --> 00:04:55,384
Hey! When you put it like that,

59
00:04:55,384 --> 00:04:58,354
you make it sound as if I used
some unscrupulous methods.

60
00:04:58,354 --> 00:05:01,991
I'm sorry. That was hardly what I meant.

61
00:05:01,991 --> 00:05:03,860
Is this our new part-timer?

62
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:04,494
What?

63
00:05:04,494 --> 00:05:07,964
I'm Onda. Nice to meet you.

64
00:05:07,964 --> 00:05:10,299
I'm the president, Riho Kaifu.

65
00:05:10,299 --> 00:05:11,868
I look forward to working
with you, Ms. Onda.

66
00:05:11,868 --> 00:05:13,165
Likewise!

67
00:05:14,103 --> 00:05:19,442
Yes, so regarding the
M&A of Midori Communications...

68
00:05:19,442 --> 00:05:23,646
Mr. Midorikawa, the largest shareholder,
is vehemently against it

69
00:05:23,646 --> 00:05:26,482
and that puts us in a
rather tough situation.

70
00:05:26,482 --> 00:05:29,252
Please be persistent and
continue to negotiate with him.

71
00:05:29,252 --> 00:05:32,221
But it seems incredibly unlikely
that he will change his mind...

72
00:05:32,221 --> 00:05:36,526
If we do not give up,
a providential wind might blow our way.

73
00:05:36,526 --> 00:05:39,362
After all, that has been true in the past.

74
00:05:39,362 --> 00:05:41,163
I understand.

75
00:05:41,163 --> 00:05:45,601
Next, on the matter of increasing
the number of host computers...

76
00:05:45,601 --> 00:05:47,803
Please take a look at the data before you.

77
00:05:47,803 --> 00:05:50,339
-Along with the expansion
of the fiber optics network,
-Oh, Ms. Riho...

78
00:05:50,339 --> 00:05:52,308
-each home...
-Oh, Ms. Riho...

79
00:05:52,308 --> 00:05:56,112
With regards to that,
you are a pro among pros.

80
00:05:56,112 --> 00:05:58,444
We will leave it entirely in your hands.

81
00:06:00,917 --> 00:06:03,386
I'm honored.

82
00:06:03,386 --> 00:06:06,355
Those directors are all idiots.

83
00:06:06,355 --> 00:06:08,949
I didn't need you to come in.

84
00:06:12,261 --> 00:06:14,697
A girl that looks like
she's in high school?

85
00:06:14,697 --> 00:06:18,501
Yes. I saw her earlier
in front of the bathroom.

86
00:06:18,501 --> 00:06:21,337
Oh, that's probably Misato.

87
00:06:21,337 --> 00:06:25,841
Misato Urano. She's supposed to be
a distant relative of Ms. Riho's.

88
00:06:25,841 --> 00:06:27,977
You'll see her around the office
from time to time.

89
00:06:27,977 --> 00:06:30,413
Misato Urano, huh?

90
00:06:30,413 --> 00:06:34,050
I think she's in her first
or second year in high school.

91
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:39,021
Her parents have passed away,
so Ms. Riho's looking after her.

92
00:06:39,021 --> 00:06:44,193
She's treated like a part-timer here.
Sort of a real world education.

93
00:06:44,193 --> 00:06:46,162
I had no idea.

94
00:06:46,162 --> 00:06:49,031
But for all that she's
related to our president,

95
00:06:49,031 --> 00:06:51,434
she's absolutely no good with computers.

96
00:06:51,434 --> 00:06:54,503
So, she's a part-timer, but about
all she does is clean, make tea,

97
00:06:54,503 --> 00:06:58,574
and act as a kind of companion
when the president is working late alone.

98
00:06:58,574 --> 00:06:59,742
I see.

99
00:06:59,742 --> 00:07:03,946
And then there's
Ms. Riho's old boyfriend...

100
00:07:03,946 --> 00:07:06,349
Hey! You're talking too much!

101
00:07:07,883 --> 00:07:10,453
Next up is news of a death.

102
00:07:10,453 --> 00:07:14,624
The former president of
Midori Communications, Raizo Midorikawa,

103
00:07:14,624 --> 00:07:17,024
still the largest shareholder, has died...

104
00:07:18,127 --> 00:07:23,366
Of the Midori Communications shares
that I, Raizo Midorikawa, own,

105
00:07:23,366 --> 00:07:28,497
I grant 75% of those shares to
President Riho Kaifu of Dead Line.

106
00:07:30,072 --> 00:07:32,408
Maybe "grant" is going too far...

107
00:07:32,408 --> 00:07:34,176
Oh, well.

108
00:07:34,176 --> 00:07:37,847
Okay, pop that on to
that old geezer's PC for me.

109
00:07:37,847 --> 00:07:40,716
Make it so it was written
maybe 10 days ago.

110
00:07:40,716 --> 00:07:44,553
I'll alter the file's
property and registry.

111
00:07:44,553 --> 00:07:46,789
So, which directory should I put it in?

112
00:07:46,789 --> 00:07:49,091
I'll leave that stuff up to you.

113
00:07:49,091 --> 00:07:54,363
Properties this, servers that.
It's all gibberish to me.

114
00:07:54,363 --> 00:07:57,332
I can't understand how people
even manage to work with PCs!

115
00:08:00,770 --> 00:08:02,670
Oh, it's time.

116
00:08:04,507 --> 00:08:06,175
"Your grievance shall be avenged.
Send"

117
00:08:06,175 --> 00:08:08,411
Make it more extreme today.

118
00:08:08,411 --> 00:08:12,279
Something they'll believe
we'd want revenge for.

119
00:08:20,790 --> 00:08:22,958
So it was uploaded by someone else...

120
00:08:22,958 --> 00:08:26,262
It's just like the Miss suspected.

121
00:08:26,262 --> 00:08:28,364
Ignoring us again?!

122
00:08:28,364 --> 00:08:31,267
Maybe Hell Girl doesn't
really exist, after all!

123
00:08:31,267 --> 00:08:35,438
Misato, go through that homepage
and find out who's behind it!

124
00:08:35,438 --> 00:08:37,606
Should be a piece of cake for you.

125
00:08:37,606 --> 00:08:39,575
Especially compared to
stealing data on new products

126
00:08:39,575 --> 00:08:42,678
or messing with account balances.

127
00:08:42,678 --> 00:08:43,612
But...

128
00:08:43,612 --> 00:08:46,916
Do you want to go back to
being the shoplifting girl?

129
00:08:46,916 --> 00:08:48,284
That's not it.

130
00:08:48,284 --> 00:08:50,853
I tried that the other day at your request,

131
00:08:50,853 --> 00:08:55,458
but instead, they came through
our firewall and almost got in.

132
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:58,094
That's not my problem!

133
00:08:58,094 --> 00:09:00,262
Shoplifting girl, huh?

134
00:09:00,262 --> 00:09:02,059
Troubling.

135
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,960
Yeah.

136
00:09:11,974 --> 00:09:15,933
"Loop"

137
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:21,183
Wow! This shop is a
subsidiary of Dead Line?!

138
00:09:21,183 --> 00:09:23,986
Huh? You know about our parent company?

139
00:09:23,986 --> 00:09:27,289
My ex-girlfriend shopped with them a lot.

140
00:09:27,289 --> 00:09:31,660
But I heard that company
only employs women.

141
00:09:31,660 --> 00:09:33,963
That even their part-timers
are all women...

142
00:09:33,963 --> 00:09:35,297
Now, they do.

143
00:09:35,297 --> 00:09:38,334
There was a time when
they had men like me, too.

144
00:09:38,334 --> 00:09:42,171
But the focus of the company
shifted towards women,

145
00:09:42,171 --> 00:09:46,575
so the men wound up
reassigned to outside subsidiaries.

146
00:09:46,575 --> 00:09:48,377
When you get down to it,
we were demoted, really.

147
00:09:48,377 --> 00:09:51,614
There's no chance we'll be
reinstated at the main office.

148
00:09:51,614 --> 00:09:56,519
Oh, that's right! I can never
go back to the main office!

149
00:09:56,519 --> 00:10:00,089
Yeah, that's what being demoted means!

150
00:10:00,089 --> 00:10:02,258
-I-I can never go back!
-S-Sir, get a hold of yourself!

151
00:10:02,258 --> 00:10:04,093
"Minato Ward Office"

152
00:10:04,093 --> 00:10:05,788
"Partial Copy of Family Register
Full Copy of Family Register
Certificate of Residence
Basic Resident Registers"

153
