"Yakitori Furusato
An Establishment with Taste
Yakitori Ramen Furusato"

155
00:10:18,374 --> 00:10:20,075
Shoplifting?

156
00:10:20,075 --> 00:10:22,771
It happens, right? Even in your store?

157
00:10:24,079 --> 00:10:26,547
Sure, every once in a while.

158
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:31,720
That reminds me, I got an
odd memo about a year ago.

159
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,855
Memo?

160
00:10:32,855 --> 00:10:35,424
Yeah, it said that if
we caught a shoplifter,

161
00:10:35,424 --> 00:10:38,961
we were to contact the president
before reporting it to the police.

162
00:10:38,961 --> 00:10:39,929
Huh.

163
00:10:39,929 --> 00:10:42,064
And then it turned out
a girl I caught in my store

164
00:10:42,064 --> 00:10:43,866
was related to the president.

165
00:10:43,866 --> 00:10:45,534
Related to the president?!

166
00:10:45,534 --> 00:10:48,938
Oh, no, no. Forget what I said.
Never mind all that.

167
00:10:48,938 --> 00:10:52,007
What?! After you told me all that?!

168
00:10:52,007 --> 00:10:54,703
Ms. Riho's told us not to talk about it.

169
00:10:55,878 --> 00:10:57,746
But...

170
00:10:57,746 --> 00:11:00,482
Maybe I will tell you.

171
00:11:00,482 --> 00:11:02,416
-What?!
-About all sorts of things!

172
00:11:10,926 --> 00:11:16,198
At the office, this girl is thought
to be useless with a computer, but...

173
00:11:16,198 --> 00:11:21,003
Nope. According to the shop owner,
she's quite the computer geek.

174
00:11:21,003 --> 00:11:22,738
She builds her own machines

175
00:11:22,738 --> 00:11:25,074
and is supposedly capable
of hacker-type work, too.

176
00:11:25,074 --> 00:11:26,308
Conversely...

177
00:11:26,308 --> 00:11:29,411
The president is no good with computers.

178
00:11:29,411 --> 00:11:31,513
Oh, you knew.

179
00:11:31,513 --> 00:11:34,717
Watching their dealings in her office,
it was easy to figure out.

180
00:11:34,717 --> 00:11:40,356
Furthermore, that girl
and Ms. Riho are not related.

181
00:11:40,356 --> 00:11:42,157
Oh, they're not?

182
00:11:42,157 --> 00:11:44,193
I checked into it during the day.

183
00:11:44,193 --> 00:11:47,763
Incidentally, the ex-boyfriend
she started the company with

184
00:11:47,763 --> 00:11:50,900
was apparently very
knowledgeable about computers.

185
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:55,037
Though, they seem to have
broken up before the company got big.

186
00:11:55,037 --> 00:11:56,338
I get it now.

187
00:11:56,338 --> 00:12:00,609
That's when she suddenly needed
someone good with computers.

188
00:12:00,609 --> 00:12:04,179
And she thought of how she could
use a shoplifter to her advantage!

189
00:12:04,179 --> 00:12:07,616
Make them help her in exchange for
not handing them over to the police.

190
00:12:07,616 --> 00:12:10,853
And she's the one that fell into that trap.

191
00:12:10,853 --> 00:12:15,916
Well, that's the sort of illegal methods
she's used to grow her company.

192
00:12:17,493 --> 00:12:18,960
Really?

193
00:12:38,547 --> 00:12:39,548
Hello?

194
00:12:39,548 --> 00:12:43,986
Hey, Misato, I just got a call
from some weird man.

195
00:12:43,986 --> 00:12:46,822
He's demanding I pay 100 million

196
00:12:46,822 --> 00:12:48,791
if I don't want the company secrets leaked.

197
00:12:48,791 --> 00:12:50,059
Is it a hacker?

198
00:12:50,059 --> 00:12:53,462
Finding that out is your job!

199
00:12:53,462 --> 00:12:54,530
You listen to me.

200
00:12:54,530 --> 00:12:59,092
Make sure you find out who he is
before I get to the office tomorrow!

201
00:13:11,347 --> 00:13:13,941
Getting in to work at this hour, eh?

202
00:13:19,221 --> 00:13:23,058
Oh, my head hurts. Must be a hang over.

203
00:13:23,058 --> 00:13:26,462
This is the issue you asked me
to handle yesterday.

204
00:13:26,462 --> 00:13:29,365
Why don't you go to school for once?

205
00:13:29,365 --> 00:13:31,500
Okay.

206
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,469
Also...

207
00:13:33,469 --> 00:13:37,206
Let's take a break from
the Hell Girl thing for a while.

208
00:13:37,206 --> 00:13:40,809
Staying up late night after night
like this isn't good for my skin.

209
00:13:40,809 --> 00:13:41,867
Okay.

210
00:13:50,152 --> 00:13:52,143
Hello? It's me!

211
00:14:01,463 --> 00:14:03,226
"Metropolitan Police Department"

212
00:14:03,465 --> 00:14:07,503
The man whose body was found
was Toru Kobayashi, age 33.

213
00:14:07,503 --> 00:14:08,731
He was in the Metropolitan area...

214
00:14:10,539 --> 00:14:14,743
The target is Toru Kobayashi, age 33.

215
00:14:14,743 --> 00:14:16,578
I'll leave the method up to you.

216
00:14:16,578 --> 00:14:18,614
Just take care of it quickly.

217
00:14:18,614 --> 00:14:20,549
At last, with this...

218
00:14:20,549 --> 00:14:22,210
At last, what?

219
00:14:24,520 --> 00:14:28,724
At last, with this, you can
get the police to arrest me?

220
00:14:28,724 --> 00:14:30,292
If I'm questioned about further crimes,

221
00:14:30,292 --> 00:14:33,853
you think they might turn up evidence
that I murdered your father, too?

222
00:14:36,965 --> 00:14:39,401
Like father, like daughter, I guess.

223
00:14:39,401 --> 00:14:41,770
The way you're both good with computers

224
00:14:41,770 --> 00:14:43,829
and the ultimate fate you'll both share!

225
00:14:45,741 --> 00:14:47,476
Your father was the same.

226
00:14:47,476 --> 00:14:49,511
In exchange for not pursuing
sexual assault charges,

227
00:14:49,511 --> 00:14:51,911
he ended up helping me.

228
00:14:52,981 --> 00:14:54,915
Not that he was guilty of those charges.

229
00:14:56,852 --> 00:14:58,410
"Copying
Remaining Time 10 Sec
Cancel"

230
00:14:59,054 --> 00:15:01,457
But his guilty conscience
got to be too much for him

231
00:15:01,457 --> 00:15:04,255
and when he tried to
report me to the police...

232
00:15:07,596 --> 00:15:09,689
...he disappeared from this world.

233
00:15:12,801 --> 00:15:15,971
It must have been tough
for you to find my company.

234
00:15:15,971 --> 00:15:20,809
After all, the fact he worked here
was strictly confidential.

235
00:15:20,809 --> 00:15:22,144
Urano...

236
00:15:22,144 --> 00:15:24,203
No, Misato Tamura!

237
00:15:25,447 --> 00:15:26,982
How...

238
00:15:26,982 --> 00:15:29,118
I can't use computers,

239
00:15:29,118 --> 00:15:34,156
but there's a handy profession
called "investigator".

240
00:15:34,156 --> 00:15:36,525
When I was having trouble
after I'd gotten rid of Tamura,

241
00:15:36,525 --> 00:15:39,328
you showed up at the perfect time.

242
00:15:39,328 --> 00:15:41,330
It got me a little suspicious.

243
00:15:41,330 --> 00:15:41,997
So I hired an investigator
and had him look into it.

244
00:15:41,997 --> 00:15:44,500
"-Cade PC Pavilion"
So I hired an investigator
